data.title: Graco Inc. appoints Andrea H. Simon to its board of directors, effective Dec. 5, 2025. Ms. Simon currently serves as Executive VP & CFO at MasterBrand, Inc.
data.description: Graco Inc. (NYSE:GGG) has recently revealed the appointment of Andrea (Andi) H. Simon to their board of directors, with the effective date being December 5, 2025. Ms. Simon currently holds the position of Executive Vice President & Chief Financial Officer at MasterBrand, Inc. (NYSE: MBC), a prominent residential cabinet manufacturer in North America. She has been in this role since 2020 and continued her position even during the 2022 spin-off of MasterBrand as an independent public entity from Fortune.

data.title: Twilio's Q3 earnings beat expectations: Revenue at $1.3 billion, up 15% YoY, with over 392,000 active customer accounts.
data.description: Twilio Inc (NYSE: TWLO) released its Q3 financial report with some significant numbers. The company's revenue for the third quarter was $1.3 billion, surpassing the projected $1.25 billion as per Benzinga Pro. Adjusted earnings for the same period stood at $1.25 per share, exceeding the estimated $1.08 per share. There was a 15% year-over-year increase in total revenue. Twilio disclosed having over 392,000 active customer accounts by September 30. The complete article can be found on Benzinga.com, discussing Twilio's growing momentum.

data.title: Apple's Q4 fiscal 2025 revenue reaches $102.5B, up 8% YoY, with $1.85 EPS, up 13% YoY, marking record earnings.
data.description: In Cupertino, California, Apple revealed its fiscal Q4 2025 financial results, ending on September 27, 2025. The company reported quarterly revenue of $102.5 billion, showing an 8% increase from the previous year. Diluted earnings per share stood at $1.85, marking a 13% rise year over year on an adjusted basis. Apple expressed pride in achieving a revenue record for the September quarter, with notable milestones including an all-time high revenue for the iPhone and the Services sector.

data.title: Amazon's Q3 results: Net sales of $180.2B (13% YoY), $1.95 EPS beats estimate. AWS revenue grew 20% to $33B.
data.description: Amazon.com reported third-quarter net sales of $180.2 billion, a 13% increase year-over-year, surpassing the $177.8 billion Street estimate. Sales were divided as North America at $106.3 billion (up 11%), International at $40.9 billion (up 14%), and AWS at $33.0 billion (up 20%). Earnings per share stood at $1.95, beating consensus by $0.38. Operating income was $17.4 billion, segmented as North America at $4.8 billion, International at $1.2 billion, and AWS at $11.4 billion. Operating income was flat compared to last year, impacted by special charges of $2.5 billion and $1.8 billion for a legal settlement and severance costs respectively.

data.title: Reddit (RDDT) beats Q3 earnings, with earnings of 80 cents per share (55% above estimates) and revenue of $585 million (7.2% above estimates).
data.description: Shares of Reddit Inc. (NYSE: RDDT) rose following the release of its Q3 earnings report after Thursday's market close, surpassing expectations on both the top and bottom lines. The stock is currently active, with detailed real-time pricing available. The company posted quarterly earnings of 80 cents per share, exceeding the projected 52 cents by 55%. Quarterly revenue stood at $585 million, outperforming the estimated $545.71 million by 7.2%. For more on Reddit's latest report, including Elon Musk's Tesla Fleet Dream, visit Benzinga.com.

data.title: Alight and IBM team up to enhance benefits admin with IBM Watson AI, enhancing employee experiences. #collaboration.

data.description: In a recent study, it was found that there has been a significant increase in cyber attacks across the globe. The data shows that there were over 4,000 reported attacks in the past year alone, which is a 30% rise from the previous year. The study also revealed that financial institutions were the most targeted, with 60% of the attacks aimed at stealing sensitive information and funds. Additionally, the research indicated that small businesses are increasingly becoming victims of cyber attacks, with a 45% increase in reported incidents. Experts are warning individuals and organizations to prioritize cybersecurity measures to protect themselves from these growing threats.
